# SPA rewrites for dynamic routes: user-generated IDs don't exist at build time,
# so we generate a `_spa` placeholder HTML per route and rewrite any real ID to it.
# The placeholder hydrates client-side and `useSpaId` reads the actual ID from
# `window.location.pathname`.
#
# Each route has THREE patterns:
#   1. `/fillings/:id/*` → `/fillings/_spa/:splat` — catches the RSC/manifest
#      files (`index.txt`, `__next.*.txt`) that Next.js fetches for client-side
#      navigation. Without this, Next.js gets 404s on those fetches and falls
#      back to a HARD navigation on every Link click, which causes AuthGate to
#      remount and flash the sign-in UI.
#   2. `/fillings/*/` → `/fillings/_spa/` — matches `/fillings/xyz/` (page URL
#      with trailing slash). The trailing slash in the pattern requires at
#      least one slash after `*`, so it cannot match `/fillings/` itself.
#   3. `/fillings/:id` → `/fillings/_spa/` — matches `/fillings/xyz` (no slash).
#      `:id` must be non-empty, so it cannot match `/fillings`.
#
# Using a single `*` without the trailing slash (e.g. `/fillings/*`) is a trap:
# the `*` glob matches empty, swallowing the list URL into the detail placeholder.
#
# NOTE ordering: nested child routes (`/production/*/products`) must come BEFORE
# the parent (`/production/*`) or the parent swallows them.

# Production batch pages (nested children first)
# IMPORTANT: Any static sub-route of /production (currently only /production/new)
# must be listed here as an explicit pass-through BEFORE the /production/:id
# catch-all — otherwise `:id` matches the literal string "new" and the static
# page is rewritten to /production/_spa/, breaking the page on Cloudflare.
# First-match-wins order: the pass-throughs below match "new" verbatim, so the
# catch-all never sees it.
/production/new/*            /production/new/:splat             200
/production/new/             /production/new/                   200
/production/new              /production/new/                   200
/production/:id/products/*   /production/_spa/products/:splat   200
/production/*/products/      /production/_spa/products/         200
/production/:id/products     /production/_spa/products/         200
/production/:id/summary/*    /production/_spa/summary/:splat    200
/production/*/summary/       /production/_spa/summary/          200
/production/:id/summary      /production/_spa/summary/          200
/production/:id/*            /production/_spa/:splat            200
/production/*/               /production/_spa/                  200
/production/:id              /production/_spa/                  200

